column1: The Lexington Traffic Management Center will be closed on Monday January 21 in observance of Dr Martin Luther King, Jr. Day.
Regular traffic reports will resume Tuesday January 22 at 6:30 a.m.

column3: Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Day Freedom March :
column4: Monday January 21 from 10 a.m. to 11 a.m. in downtown Lexington.

column3: Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Day Freedom March :
column4: Rolling street closures starting on Vine St at Broadway, proceeding to Rose St, to E Main St, and back to Main at Broadway.
